play shows \"Isolated Sovereign Node Compute Allocation\" when invoice.description is undefined, and that's precisely what I wanted to achieve.\n\n\n**Implementing Invoice List States**\n\nI'm now integrating states for loading, error, and invoice data within the invoice list component. My immediate task is fetching data from `/api/v1/invoices` on component mount using the JWT token and rendering the appropriate states. I'm focusing on price formatting for correct display and updating the `filteredInvoices` logic. I'm also ensuring copying functionalities work properly with the invoice hash and the drawer integrates correctly with deep audit. I'm also doing a dry run of the overall `/app/portal/billing/page.tsx`'s structure and its imports, including the validation of `useRouter` where applicable.\n\n\n**Evaluating Login Redirection**\n\nI'm now determining the most effective approach for handling unauthenticated users in `/app/portal/billing/page.tsx`. I can import `useRouter` to implement redirection, which would improve error handling. However, I can also display an error message and provide a login link using standard `<Link>`. I'm also adding `useEffect` and `useCallback` to the existing imports, and preparing to inspect how the `invoices` array is rendered within `/app/portal/billing/page.tsx`.\n\nI've got the logic for managing unauthenticated users in `/app/portal/billing/page.tsx` now.\n\n\n**Fetching Invoice Data Dynamically**\n\nI'm now replacing the static invoice array with a dynamic `invoices` state. I'm introducing `loading` and `error` states for a more robust data fetching experience within the invoice list component. My immediate goal is to fetch invoice data from the API upon component mount, and then render it within `/app/portal/billing/page.tsx` properly. I need to make sure the data updates correctly in the drawer. I'm focusing on the `selInvoice`'s rendering.\n\n\n**Refining Invoice Drawer Logic**\n\nI'm now integrating the invoice hash display and copy functionality within the drawer component. I'm focusing on the `handleCopy` function and ensuring the `selInvoice.hash` is correctly rendered in the dedicated `<div>`. I've added a button to close the drawer, that is working as expected. Next, I will be working on the specific details in the drawer, focusing on the visual styling.\n\n\n**Enhancing Invoice Drawer Display**\n\nI'm now focusing on the detailed display within the invoice drawer. I'm targeting the formatting and presentation of specific invoice details. My plan is to implement a robust display of the invoice details for `category`, `amount`, and `currency`. The `toLocaleString` method will be critical, ensuring the amount's precise formatting and display. I'll include the `issue_date` for timestamp, ensuring all data is present and correctly formatted.\n\n\n**Formatting Due Date Display**\n\nI'm now focusing on formatting and integrating the `due_date` in the invoice drawer. I'm ensuring its proper rendering alongside existing invoice details. I also need to make sure `selInvoice.due_date` is displayed within the drawer, to complete the visual elements.\n\n\n**Integrating Due Date Display**\n\nI'm now integrating the `due_date` within the invoice details. I'm focusing on ensuring its precise and user-friendly formatting within the invoice drawer, and aligning it with existing invoice details and formatting. I need to make sure the date is correctly rendered, and that I'm also including all visual elements for proper display. I'm leveraging the current components for formatting.\n\n\n"}}
